VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \bnew\s+\w+(?![^<>]*\s*>)
WHEN EXPR MISSING:free\s*\(|delete\s+|unique_ptr|shared_ptr|RAII
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects dynamic memory allocation using `new` but no matching `delete`, potentially leading to memory leaks.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Potential Memory Leak: Use of `new` Without `delete`.
